Preheat oven to 350 degrees F. Drain 1 can tomatoes and set aside. Heat a large skillet over medium-high heat. Brown beef, stirring frequently. Add 1 can tomatoes and its liquid, 1/2 of the drained tomatoes, the refried beans and chili powder. Stir until well blended. Cook 5 minutes or until beginning to boil, stirring occasionally. Place in shallow 2-1/2-quart baking dish. Sprinkle the remaining tomatoes evenly over all and top with corn and cheese. Bake 8-10 minutes or until cheese is melted. Garnish with cilantro and sour cream, if desired. Serve warm with tortilla chips.